1
00:00:55,859 --> 00:00:56,859
Move!

2
00:00:58,500 --> 00:00:59,659
What did you say?

3
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:02,630
- Move!
- I can't hear you.

4
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:06,439
I can't hear you.

5
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:08,909
I said, move!

6
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:11,310
I can't hear you.

7
00:01:41,569 --> 00:01:43,370
- Did you order jjajangmyeon?
- Yes.

8
00:01:50,980 --> 00:01:52,849
- It looks so good.
- Here's your jjajangmyeon.

9
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:54,150
Thank you.

10
00:02:00,590 --> 00:02:02,489
- What's that man doing?
- Why is he exercising here?

11
00:02:29,090 --> 00:02:30,919
Are you repaying me for
helping you on the rooftop?

12
00:02:32,590 --> 00:02:35,060
Are you all right?
You didn't get hurt, did you?

13
00:02:35,889 --> 00:02:37,759
No, I'm totally fine.

14
00:02:38,629 --> 00:02:40,199
The courier arrived.

15
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:41,530
Courier?

16
00:02:41,569 --> 00:02:44,699
By the way,
did these get damaged at all?

17
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:53,139
Ro Woon! Ro Woon.
Did the courier arrive?

18
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,610
Yes, I have them here. Gosh...

19
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:58,080
Why is this here?

20
00:02:58,150 --> 00:03:00,449
- Be gentle. Treat it like a baby.
- Yes!

21
00:03:00,490 --> 00:03:01,889
Of course. Sure thing.

22
00:03:02,189 --> 00:03:04,090
This is a lot more valuable...

23
00:03:05,819 --> 00:03:08,189
than me.

24
00:03:08,930 --> 00:03:11,229
Let me see. My goodness.

25
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:13,430
My gosh.

26
00:03:15,099 --> 00:03:16,770
This is...

27
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,780
- Hey, run.
- Here they are.

28
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:26,340
- You need to apologize, too.
- Here.

29
00:03:26,439 --> 00:03:28,979
- I apologize. I'm so sorry.
- We can resume the shoot soon.

30
00:03:29,110 --> 00:03:30,620
- We'll resume the shoot shortly.
- I'm so sorry.

31
00:03:30,650 --> 00:03:31,979
- We apologize.
- I'm sorry.

32
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:33,479
- Apologize.
- My deepest apologies.

33
00:03:33,889 --> 00:03:35,120
I'm really sorry.

34
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:55,569
(Episode 3:
I'm Not an Easygoing Person)

35
00:03:55,610 --> 00:04:00,310
(Episode 3:
I'm Not an Easygoing Person)

36
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,949
You said you'll take
responsibility for this.

37
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:08,689
You better keep your word.

38
00:04:16,730 --> 00:04:18,100
This can be fixed, right?

39
00:04:23,230 --> 00:04:25,939
I should just think of it
as a gift for myself.

40
00:04:26,069 --> 00:04:29,470
(New York Barbershop)

41
00:04:53,259 --> 00:04:54,329
Did you eat?

42
00:04:55,399 --> 00:04:56,529
Yes.

43
00:05:05,279 --> 00:05:08,709
Ji Hye, the house without you...

44
00:05:10,079 --> 00:05:11,379
is silent.

45
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:17,389
It's like an empty house
no one lives in.

46
00:05:32,939 --> 00:05:34,310
(Chae Ji Hye)

47
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:04,439
Don't worry.

48
00:06:08,370 --> 00:06:09,509
Our revenge...

49
00:06:10,939 --> 00:06:12,339
is just beginning.

50
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:22,790
Did you hear?

51
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:25,790
The penthouse will be opened.

52
00:06:26,259 --> 00:06:27,689
No way. Are you serious?

53
00:06:27,959 --> 00:06:30,360
- Yes. They started renovations.
- Seriously?

54
00:06:30,860 --> 00:06:32,930
- Who told you?
- Ms. Park.

55
00:06:33,029 --> 00:06:34,029
What?

56
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:36,399
Ms. Park?

57
00:07:01,490 --> 00:07:02,560
You're here.

58
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:13,199
Why did it have to be here?

59
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:17,480
It's your father's orders.

60
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,339
This space felt overpowering before.

61
00:07:21,009 --> 00:07:22,379
No, not here.

62
00:07:22,410 --> 00:07:25,120
Then do you want to share the space
with the staff downstairs?

63
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:29,689
That's what we should do.
We'll just get you a partition.

64
00:07:31,689 --> 00:07:33,290
It'll still be better for you here.

65
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:38,160
Thanks for being courageous,
Hwan Gi.

66
00:07:39,029 --> 00:07:40,629
I thought you would
keep on saying no.

67
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:45,240
I'll gladly take the heat.

68
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:48,139
Take the heat? What heat?

69
00:07:48,769 --> 00:07:50,339
This is a new beginning
and a new challenge.

70
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:55,050
I made sure to pick elites to keep
the number of your teammates low.

71
00:07:55,410 --> 00:07:56,949
I bet no one applied for it.

72
00:07:57,620 --> 00:08:00,620
It's not like that.
The position is too big for them.

73
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:02,750
Forget it.
I have a few people in mind.

74
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:04,360
You do?

75
00:08:05,019 --> 00:08:06,060
Do you even know our employees?

76
00:08:06,089 --> 00:08:07,730
Sorry I'm late.

77
00:08:07,759 --> 00:08:08,930
Her hobby is being late.

78
00:08:08,959 --> 00:08:10,329
- Your bread is here.
- I want bread.

79
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,699
Her specialty is buying bread.

80
00:08:11,899 --> 00:08:15,970
I had to take a complaint from
our client since you weren't here.

81
00:08:17,339 --> 00:08:20,709
- I love you, Ms. Jung.
- She's the mom of the office.

82
00:08:20,939 --> 00:08:23,240
She values people
and relationships over work.

83
00:08:28,009 --> 00:08:31,220
Gosh, this report is...

84
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,580
too schematic.

85
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:35,220
His hobby and talent
are spoiling the mood.

86
00:08:35,450 --> 00:08:37,919
He's always nagging
from a step behind.

87
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,159
That report is too...

88
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:41,059
- Gosh, you reek of alcohol.
- Gosh.

89
00:08:41,490 --> 00:08:43,360
- You two...
- Please go away.

90
00:08:44,129 --> 00:08:47,500
Both had poor performance for three
years, and will likely be let go.

91
00:08:48,029 --> 00:08:50,470
If you are going to fire them,
send them to me.

92
00:08:50,639 --> 00:08:52,070
You have no idea.

93
00:08:52,669 --> 00:08:53,909
You don't know our employees.

94
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:56,740
I love you, Ms. Jung.

95
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:59,809
She's known as "Yoo Hee Call Center"
at the office.

96
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:02,649
She always treats everyone
with love and care.

97
00:09:03,149 --> 00:09:05,250
She knows her colleagues'
love life, married life,

98
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:08,350
and even family matters.

99
00:09:08,690 --> 00:09:10,690
Right, don't eat this.

100
00:09:10,889 --> 00:09:13,220
It's your ex-boyfriend's wedding
this weekend, right?

101
00:09:15,230 --> 00:09:17,360
You're pretty now,
but lose a bit more weight.

102
00:09:17,559 --> 00:09:19,500
Make sure you dress up.

103
00:09:20,159 --> 00:09:22,200
Before she became a mother
and lost her mind,

104
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,769
her project portfolios
looked promising.

105
00:09:26,039 --> 00:09:27,039
Eat this.

106
00:09:28,570 --> 00:09:30,139
Taking a step back...

107
00:09:30,809 --> 00:09:32,309
means that he can see something
others cannot.

108
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:33,840
This report is...

109
00:09:34,809 --> 00:09:36,149
too schematic.

110
00:09:36,379 --> 00:09:38,250
You all need to study more.

111
00:09:38,620 --> 00:09:41,350
How can you take money
from the company working like that?

112
00:09:41,519 --> 00:09:44,419
You can't nag someone
without being knowledgeable.

113
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,659
When did you figure all that out?

114
00:09:51,029 --> 00:09:52,799
There is one more. Kim Gyo Ri.

115
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:55,629
Kim Gyo Ri? Ms. Kim?

116
00:09:55,830 --> 00:09:58,500
She first applied as an AE.
Do you not remember?

117
00:10:02,639 --> 00:10:04,080
(Kim Gyo Ri)

118
00:10:04,110 --> 00:10:07,580
I'm a quiet person,

119
00:10:08,950 --> 00:10:13,850
but I want to show that a quiet
person can PR in a quiet way...

120
00:10:14,450 --> 00:10:19,720
through quiet means. I think?

121
00:10:20,460 --> 00:10:22,590
- Are you set on being an AE?
- Pardon?

122
00:10:26,629 --> 00:10:30,399
No. I'll do my best
in whatever you assign me.

123
00:10:36,909 --> 00:10:39,440
Wouldn't it be uncomfortable
for both of you?

124
00:10:40,039 --> 00:10:43,149
This is all a show to quiet down
the criticism about abusing power.

125
00:10:43,879 --> 00:10:45,179
It'll be good for our publicity.

126
00:10:45,919 --> 00:10:47,690
If that's what you want, sure.

127
00:10:48,519 --> 00:10:51,860
I have two people picked out,
so that's five in total.

128
00:10:52,460 --> 00:10:53,690
Three is enough for me.

129
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,730
I have authority over HR.

130
00:10:56,490 --> 00:10:59,230
Come on,
I'm letting you have your way.

131
00:10:59,460 --> 00:11:01,470
You get 3, and I get 2.

132
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:04,769
- Who are they?
- It's a secret for now.

133
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:06,399
You can look forward to it.

134
00:11:12,779 --> 00:11:14,350
- You.
- Chae Ro Woon.

135
00:11:18,049 --> 00:11:19,419
What are you doing here?

136
00:11:19,519 --> 00:11:21,289
I got hired, too.

137
00:11:22,389 --> 00:11:23,419
What is this?

138
00:11:24,059 --> 00:11:26,759
I thought Brain was
the best PR agency in Korea.

139
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:29,159
It must be a lie
since they hired us.

140
00:11:31,559 --> 00:11:33,659
- Wait, wait.
- Hold on.

141
00:11:34,269 --> 00:11:36,700
- Hello.
- Hello.

142
00:11:36,899 --> 00:11:38,139
- Hello.
- Which floor are you going?

143
00:11:38,899 --> 00:11:40,169
I told you I'm stalking you.

144
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,139
I'm in your department.
I begged for it.

145
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,470
To whom?

146
00:11:43,509 --> 00:11:44,809
To my mom.

147
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:48,379
Call your mom back...

148
00:11:48,850 --> 00:11:51,019
and tell her
to put you somewhere else.

149
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:52,279
Why?

150
00:12:07,830 --> 00:12:10,970
Why did it have to be us?

151
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:16,070
It's their way
of indirectly telling us...

152
00:12:17,779 --> 00:12:19,210
to leave the company.

153
00:12:21,980 --> 00:12:23,850
I didn't know
I'd end up working here again.

154
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,820
Aren't you happy that I'm here?

155
00:12:28,850 --> 00:12:31,690
- Stop it.
- I know you are.

156
00:12:34,019 --> 00:12:36,230
What are you doing out here?
Let's go in.

157
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:43,870
Now, for the last member...

158
00:12:44,470 --> 00:12:46,840
It's someone we need for
Brain's first in-house venture...

159
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:50,940
and for the PI project of clearing
Eun Hwan Gi's name.

160
00:12:51,740 --> 00:12:55,679
The only person that can make you
run around like a headless chicken.

161
00:12:57,950 --> 00:12:59,779
- She can't be here.
- I should correct myself.

162
00:13:00,889 --> 00:13:01,950
Besides your father that is.

163
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:03,549
No, not her.

164
00:13:27,409 --> 00:13:29,080
You're just in time.

165
00:13:41,129 --> 00:13:43,190
Hey, everyone is here.

166
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,500
Here. Come on.

167
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:49,700
Say hello.

168
00:13:51,669 --> 00:13:53,940
What? The delivery man?

169
00:13:54,769 --> 00:13:55,970
Do you want me to introduce you?

170
00:13:58,139 --> 00:13:59,940
All right, let me introduce him.

171
00:14:00,809 --> 00:14:03,279
He's the boss of our newly launched
Silent Monster.

172
00:14:05,220 --> 00:14:06,379
Eun Hwan Gi.

173
00:14:13,019 --> 00:14:15,230
Hello, nice to meet you.

174
00:14:16,990 --> 00:14:19,299
- Hello.
- Hello.

175
00:14:23,769 --> 00:14:26,940
It... It can't be.

176
00:14:27,769 --> 00:14:30,980
Mr. Kang, you were there that day.
He came by that motorcycle.

177
00:14:31,710 --> 00:14:32,879
Well, I'm not sure.

178
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:35,250
I've never seen him on a motorcycle.

179
00:14:35,279 --> 00:14:38,379
That's because it's not allowed to
ride a motorcycle in that park.

180
00:14:38,580 --> 00:14:41,289
That's why he had to run there.

181
00:14:41,450 --> 00:14:43,620
So he...

182
00:14:44,759 --> 00:14:47,389
He then...

183
00:14:47,490 --> 00:14:49,129
What are you trying to say?

184
00:14:49,490 --> 00:14:50,929
What did he do?

185
00:14:51,230 --> 00:14:53,629
He tried to...

186
00:14:56,899 --> 00:14:57,940
What is this?

187
00:14:59,470 --> 00:15:00,700
I need to talk to you.

188
00:15:03,769 --> 00:15:07,309
Sorry. Please get to know
each other first.

189
00:15:09,210 --> 00:15:10,350
Is he our boss?

190
00:15:10,379 --> 00:15:12,320
Did something happen between him
and you? What about a motorcycle?

191
00:15:12,419 --> 00:15:13,480
No.

192
00:15:13,519 --> 00:15:15,649
I'm surprised, too.

193
00:15:16,049 --> 00:15:18,289
He looks better than I expected.

194
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:20,990
He looks like a typical rich kid.

195
00:15:21,559 --> 00:15:23,330
While his employees are
slaving away,

196
00:15:23,490 --> 00:15:26,629
he's been having this palace
all to himself.

197
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,399
How much money would have
gone into all this?

198
00:15:32,799 --> 00:15:34,970
- Send her away.
- Hey.

199
00:15:35,009 --> 00:15:36,940
She just entered the company.
It was just a small mistake.

200
00:15:36,970 --> 00:15:38,480
It's a good enough reason
to fire her.

201
00:15:39,179 --> 00:15:41,179
Technically, the one to blame is...

202
00:15:41,409 --> 00:15:43,750
the clumsy novice courier.

203
00:15:44,110 --> 00:15:46,480
Anyway, she can't stay.
Especially near me.

204
00:15:46,879 --> 00:15:48,549
Why?

205
00:15:48,990 --> 00:15:50,289
If my cover gets blown,

206
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:52,820
she might get hurt.

207
00:15:52,860 --> 00:15:55,759
Is there something about her
only you know about?

208
00:15:55,789 --> 00:15:56,960
She's loud.

209
00:15:57,659 --> 00:15:58,659
I know.

210
00:15:59,330 --> 00:16:01,799
She's the loud type of person
you hate.

211
00:16:01,970 --> 00:16:02,970
But...

212
00:16:03,370 --> 00:16:06,669
she's cheerful and energetic
just like I used to be.

213
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,240
I like her.

214
00:16:08,769 --> 00:16:09,909
You like her?

215
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:13,379
- What do you know about her?
- I could see at once...

216
00:16:13,679 --> 00:16:15,610
that she's just like me.

217
00:16:17,679 --> 00:16:19,720
You don't know
what she's hiding inside her.

218
00:16:26,559 --> 00:16:27,889
Have you two already become close?

219
00:16:28,659 --> 00:16:31,659
She's so feisty that she might
make you feel uncomfortable,

220
00:16:31,860 --> 00:16:33,960
but it's just that she likes
people so much like a puppy does.

221
00:16:34,629 --> 00:16:37,330
People like her rarely
get hurt by others.

222
00:16:37,669 --> 00:16:40,200
She's more hurt than anyone else is.

223
00:16:41,169 --> 00:16:44,139
That means she's perfect
for a cat like you.

224
00:16:44,509 --> 00:16:48,149
You admit that you easily
hurt others, don't you?

225
00:16:48,210 --> 00:16:50,610
- Still...
- If you're still uncomfortable,

226
00:16:51,980 --> 00:16:54,850
trust me. I'll help her out.

227
00:16:54,950 --> 00:16:56,190
Still, I prefer to be alone.

228
00:16:56,220 --> 00:16:57,820
If you still want her to leave,

229
00:16:58,720 --> 00:16:59,960
tell her yourself.

230
00:17:03,259 --> 00:17:04,259
I'm getting off.

231
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:06,730
- Let me come with you.
- Hold on.

232
00:17:15,539 --> 00:17:16,670
She's your employee.

233
00:17:17,309 --> 00:17:19,109
You're responsible for her.

234
00:17:31,119 --> 00:17:33,960
The clumsy courier
turns out to be...

235
00:17:34,630 --> 00:17:36,859
the psychopath, Eun Hwan Gi?

236
00:17:37,859 --> 00:17:39,299
I'm sorry.

237
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:41,630
I'm sorry.

238
00:17:41,970 --> 00:17:44,799
What were those eyes?

239
00:17:56,349 --> 00:17:59,079
If you still want her to leave,
tell her yourself.

240
00:18:19,170 --> 00:18:20,269
Excuse me.

241
00:18:21,309 --> 00:18:24,210
Why don't we wait
until Mr. Eun says something?

242
00:18:25,609 --> 00:18:27,480
What is
this uncomfortable atmosphere?

243
00:18:27,579 --> 00:18:29,109
Why isn't anyone saying anything?

244
00:18:29,509 --> 00:18:30,680
What?

245
00:18:30,710 --> 00:18:31,880
Gosh.

246
00:18:43,130 --> 00:18:45,930
I shouldn't embarrass her
in front of everyone.

247
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,269
Could you...

248
00:18:50,230 --> 00:18:51,839
give us some room?

249
00:18:52,970 --> 00:18:54,299
- What did he say?
- Room?

250
00:18:54,339 --> 00:18:55,670
- What did he say?
- Can you hear him?

251
00:18:55,710 --> 00:18:56,740
No.

252
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:58,579
We can't hear you.

253
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:07,349
Could you leave your desks?

254
00:19:07,849 --> 00:19:10,650
- Desks?
- Is there something wrong?

255
00:19:12,059 --> 00:19:15,160
I'm afraid we need to...

256
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:17,460
remove a desk.

257
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:18,960
What about desks?

258
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:21,430
I think he wants us to
move the desks.

259
00:19:21,470 --> 00:19:23,130
That makes sense.

260
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,470
He's sitting so far away from us.

261
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,000
We can't hear him well.

262
00:19:27,099 --> 00:19:30,369
Everyone, stand up.

263
