how we'll call each other?

315
00:23:02,450 --> 00:23:04,650
I heard, at ventures,

316
00:23:04,690 --> 00:23:07,190
you call each other by
the first name.

317
00:23:07,289 --> 00:23:08,559
I'm sure it has good intentions,

318
00:23:09,029 --> 00:23:11,029
but it's not something
we're used to.

319
00:23:11,130 --> 00:23:12,430
Don't you think so, Yoo Hee?

320
00:23:13,660 --> 00:23:14,660
Well...

321
00:23:15,230 --> 00:23:18,200
It does make me feel young,

322
00:23:18,299 --> 00:23:19,299
Sun Bong.

323
00:23:21,069 --> 00:23:22,640
That's American style.

324
00:23:23,839 --> 00:23:27,109
We shouldn't call Mr. Eun
Mr. Eun, either.

325
00:23:28,210 --> 00:23:31,180
Still, we couldn't call him
by his first name.

326
00:23:31,619 --> 00:23:34,380
She's right. He's the head of
Silent Monster.

327
00:23:34,450 --> 00:23:38,049
Let's just call him Mr. Eun.

328
00:23:38,089 --> 00:23:40,319
I'm up for calling him
by first name.

329
00:23:40,619 --> 00:23:41,960
It'll be awkward,

330
00:23:41,990 --> 00:23:45,329
but I think it sounds
more respectful for some reason.

331
00:23:45,359 --> 00:23:47,000
Gyo Ri, how about you give it a try?

332
